# HoloRobust

**Holographic & Geometric Physics-Informed Robust ML Framework**

[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)
[![Python 3.11+](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.11+-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/)
[![PyTorch](https://img.shields.io/badge/PyTorch-2.0+-red.svg)](https://pytorch.org/)

HoloRobust is an open-source PyTorch framework that injects deep ideas from **string theory**, **AdS/CFT holography**, **holographic QCD**, and **Lorentzian Arakelov geometry** directly into modern machine learning — producing models that are more robust, more physically meaningful, and more resistant to adversarial attack.

---

## What It Does

Standard neural networks learn from data alone. HoloRobust adds physics structure from holography and arithmetic geometry into the training process, making models:

- **Adversarially robust** — trained simultaneously against PGD attacks
- **Physically meaningful** — latent spaces shaped by AdS/CFT and Arakelov geometry
- **Deployment-ready** — ONNX and TorchScript export, FPGA-compatible via hls4ml
- **Better anomaly detectors** — physics constraints separate signal from background more cleanly

---

## Applications

| Domain | Task | Method |
|--------|------|--------|
| High-Energy Physics | Jet anomaly detection, LHC trigger | Holographic autoencoder |
| Cybersecurity | Adversarially robust intrusion detection | Physics-informed anomaly scoring |
| Edge / FPGA | Low-latency inference (<200μs) | ONNX → hls4ml pipeline |

