## Project Structure

```
holorobust/
├── holorobust/
│   ├── core/
│   │   ├── model.py       # HoloRobustModel base class
│   │   └── trainer.py     # Unified physics + adversarial trainer
│   ├── holographic/
│   │   └── losses.py      # AdS/CFT holographic regularizers
│   ├── geometric/
│   │   └── losses.py      # Arakelov geometric regularizers
│   └── utils/
│       └── export.py      # ONNX, TorchScript, latency benchmark
└── examples/
    └── hep_jet_anomaly.ipynb  # LHC anomaly detection demo
```

---

## Use Cases

**High-Energy Physics**
Real-time anomaly detection for LHC experiments. The encoder exports to ONNX
and compiles to FPGA firmware via hls4ml, making it deployable at Level-1
trigger rates. Physics losses enforce conservation-law-consistent latent spaces.

**Cybersecurity**
Adversarially robust anomaly detection for network intrusion detection.
Models trained with HoloRobust maintain detection performance under
adversarial evasion attacks that fool standard autoencoders.

